/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:31:- The step quietly assumes a perturbative principle that the mission context already warns against. Exact Beltrami cancellation is known to be extremely fragile. Localizing the condition to high-vorticity regions does not cure that fragility, because the strain and pressure are nonlocal.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:33:- "Using exact-Beltrami cancellation as the anchor case" risks importing De Giorgi/pressure intuition into a vorticity-stretching problem. The two phenomena are related only indirectly. This step needs a direct path from local alignment to control of `S omega`, not a memory of a different cancellation.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:43:- The phrase "identify the exact missing lemma" is too optimistic. The obstruction is unlikely to be one missing lemma. It is more likely a whole package: propagation of local alignment, stability of tube coherence across scales, and a nonlocal estimate that turns deficit control into `S omega` control.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:47:This step should be judged by a much stricter standard: does it create a genuinely new implication from local Beltrami geometry to a known regularity mechanism? If not, it should terminate as a negative result, not be upgraded into a "draft proposition."
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:60:- The chain conflates Beltrami alignment, vorticity-direction coherence, and tube persistence. They are related heuristically, not quantitatively. Treating them as one mechanism is the central structural flaw.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:63:- The success criterion is too forgiving. "Conditional statement or conjecture" is cheap. The chain should count as success only if it proves a new scale-appropriate bridge from local Beltrami deficit to an existing regularity criterion, or else a rigorous obstruction showing why no such bridge exists.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:64:- There is partial prior-art redundancy. Without a hard Beltrami-to-criterion bridge, the chain collapses back into known Constantin-Fefferman style regularity conditions plus suggestive tube language.
